  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver employs a power-law hemolysis damage accumulation model whose behaviour depends on three tunable parameters: the base mesh element size (target 0.15 mm near blade surfaces), a scalar stress-weighting threshold (set to 50 Pa during validation runs), and a temporal integration sub-step count (32 sub-steps per impeller revolution at the chosen settings). Validation results are reported at these chosen settings; no configuration node pins or documents these values for deployment use.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2-req",
